//THERAPY SWITCH EVENT

"ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.1": "I'm sorry, Shane. This typically wouldn't be a problem, #$b# But my colleague did say that it was important for you to go so you aren't so isolated.",
"ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.2": "Are there any others that I could join?$3",
"ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.3": "Not this season, and not as frequent.$2 #$b# We could put possibly put you in AA instead, and it's in the same building.",
    "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.4": "Not on the same day, right?",
    "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.5": "Shane, is there... something wrong with the group therapy sessions?$2",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.6": "No.",
 "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.7": "Are you sure? Because I heard-—$2",
"ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.8": "You're gonna listen to rumours now?$5",
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.9": "Well, when it comes to the wellbeing of a child, I do have the right to break confidentiality.$5", 
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.10": "Someone had mentioned to me that Jas has been... acting strange.$2 #$b# She's quiet, well, quieter than usual. Wandering off on her own...$2 #$b# Is everything okay with you and your aunt at home?$2",
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.11": "Marnie and I... haven't been talking much...$2 #$b# We don't argue in front of Jas but, the kid is smart.$2",
     "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.12": "Children are perceptive to things like that.",
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.13": "Tell me about it. #$b# Unless I was playing gridball, all my parents did was argue.$3",
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.14": "I believe you and your aunt mentioned that before when I arrived...$2 #$b# But, you said that your aunt's farm was a safe place for you growing up. #$b# Is there any reason why you and your aunt aren't getting along?",
       "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.15": "Marnie keeps pushing me about talking to someone from my past.$2 #$b# But I can't...$2", 
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.16": "I see. Does this person have anything to do with your drinking?$2", 
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.17": "No, nothing like that.", 
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.18": "And... is this person in therapy with you?$2",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.19": "Shane, therapy is meant to help you. #$b# If you don't talk in therapy, and someone there is causing you distress, then I can't in good conscience recommend you continue.$2 #$b# I don't mean to sound like a broken record echoing your aunt,$1 #$b# But, would it make you feel better to talk to them?",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.20": "I don't know...$2 #$b# I guess I don't know what to even say to them. They've...changed. #$b# And... I don't want to add to their plate.$3", 
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.21": "You're both in therapy, change of some kind is the goal, isn't it? #$b# Group therapy is about taking things off your plate, and sharing it with everyone so it's easier to manage in smaller bites. #$b# That way, you're able to take more and it won't feel as heavy.$1",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.22": "Did you miss lunch or something, doc?$3",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.23": "Gus' niece, Rosalie, is dropping me off something this afternoon.$1 #$b# I guess I am a bit more famished than I thought!$1",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.24": "Oh... that's nice...$11",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.25": "How about this Shane, give it another week. #$b# Try and see if you and this person can work things out. #$b# If you still feel you need to change groups, I'll contact my colleague and see if we can figure something out.",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.26": "No, don't worry about it...$3 #$b# I'll... Figure something out. Thanks, Doc.",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.27": "Dr H! Your girlfriend's here for lunch!$1",
        "ShaneRosalieTherapySwitchEvent.28": "Oh! What great timing!$4 #$b# WAIT! I DIDN'T--$8 #$b# Rosalie isn't-- We're not---!$8 #$b# Ahem...$2 #$b# Please tell her to come in, I'm just finishing up here with a patient.$5",

 

       



    //ROSALIE'S RIBBON EVENT(S)
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.1": "Oh! Hi, @! This is an unexpected visit! Need anything for the farm?",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2": "What?! She let me have it?! #$b# THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU!!!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.3": "Uncle Shane! Uncle Shane! Look at my new ribbon!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.4": "Wow, Jas! That's real pretty!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.5": "Uh huh!$1 #$b# Farmer @ told the pretty new girl that I liked her ribbon, and she gave it to me!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.6": "...$10 #$b#...$3 #$b# What uh... what new girl?$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.7": "I think her name was...$3 #$b# ... Rose... Rosa...$3...!$1 #$b# Rosa! I'm sure of it!$4",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.8": "I see...$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.Q": "@, are you sure... she said Jas could keep it?",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A1": "Are you calling me a liar?",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A2": "Yes! Isn't that nice?",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A3": "No, I stole it off of Rosalie's head and came straight here to frame Jas. Police are on their way.",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A1R": "No, no... Just... checking...$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A2R": "Yeah... Nice...$11",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.A3R": "That's not very funny, @.$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.9": "Uncle Shane, am I in trouble?$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.10": "No! No, of course not!$6 #$b# I'm glad you made a new friend today!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.11": "I'm gonna wear it every day, just like Miss Rosa does!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.12": "Shane, you should probably tell her thank you.$0",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.13Gender": "$query PLAYER_GENDER Current Female#Thank you.$3|Who?$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.14": "You know who I mean, Shane.$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.15": "Shane, we don't know how long Rosalie's going to be in town for...$2 #$b# You should talk to her.",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.16": "I have talked to her.$11 #$b# I... said 'hi' to her in therapy.$11",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.17": "Shane, is this because of what happened before she left?$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.18": "Of course not!$5 #$b# In fact, I forgot all about it until you mentioned it just now...$11",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.19": "Thanks for um... getting the gift for Jas, @.$3 #$b# I gotta go.",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.20": "*sigh* Well, if he's going to the saloon, maybe he'll talk to her now...$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.21": "I'm sorry, @. It's nothing personal, and you did nothing wrong!$1 #$b# Shane and Rosalie just have a... complicated history.$2 #$b# Anyway, thank you again! You made Jas' week!$1",
 
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.0": "Rosa.",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.1": "Oh my Yoba!$8 #$b# Shane, don't sneak up on me like that! You know I'm jumpy!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.2": "Sorry, Rosa...$2#$b# But, if you wanted to talk to me, you didn't have to use Jas or @ to do it.$5",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.3": "Okay, um... Nice to see you too in between group therapy and bus rides.$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.4": "That's it?$5#$b# Twenty years, you get Jas and @ involved, and that's all you have to say to me?$5",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.5": "What do you want me to say to you, Farm Boy?$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.6": "Buh... Forget it. Never mind.$3",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.7": "Wait, Shane, are you mad?!",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.8": "No.$11",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.9": "You so are! I can tell!$1 #$b# You still press your lips into a line when you're mad!$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.10":"Yeah, I guess I do...$6 #$b# I never noticed.$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.11": "Who's Jas?$2 #$b# Was she the little girl? #$b# @ came by and said she liked it and I thought she'd like to have it.$1",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.12": "I didn't mean to get her in trouble or start anything.$2 #$b# I didn't know she was your kid, honest.$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.13": "She's not my kid...$3 #$b# I mean, she is but...",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.14": "Aunt Marnie and I are her guardians. I'm her godfather. #$b# Her parents were friends of mine...$0",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.15": "I see... I'm sorry...$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.16": "I noticed Jas had been looking at my ribbon since I arrived. #$b# I thought maybe she was too shy to say anything and was more comfortable asking @ since you two are close. #$b# I didn't mean to offend you, honest.$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.17": "It's all good. Sorry for coming in hot like that.$1 #$b# You didn't offend me.$6 #$b# I just thought...$2",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.18": "Yeah?",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.19": "I just thought...$2 #$b#... I should thank you.$3 #$b# So um... Thank you, Rosa.$6",
    "ShaneRosalieJasRibbonEvent.2.20": "You're welcome, Farm Boy.$1",


//Rosalie Sneeze Event

"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.1": "Hi, @! You're right on time. Dinner is just about ready.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.2": "Hey, @! #$b# I was just about to say things are weirdly quiet today...$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.3": "Marnie, where's Jas? She should have been back from Vincent's by now.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.4": "Huh, I did tell her to be home by four...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.5": "There you are!$1 #$b# ...$10",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.6": "Um... Hi, Rosa...$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.7": "Hello, Farm Boy.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.Q1": "You look between Rosalie and Shane as they try not to look at each other.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1": "Ask who is 'Rosa' and 'Farm Boy'.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A2": "Ask why Jas was late coming home.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.1": "It's... a long story.$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.2": "Well, I can tell it! #$b# Shane and I were besties when we were kids.$1 #$b# The nick names are just a little inside joke we have. Well, and Marnie and now Jas call me 'Rosa', too.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.3": "Can I have a cool nickname?$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.4": "You already have a nickname! Jas is short for Jasmine!",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.5": "But I want one like Rosa and Farm Boy!$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.6": "Let's just stick to calling me 'Uncle Shane'...$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.7": "How about...$9 #$b# Minnie!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.8": "Why 'Minnie'?",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.9": "Her name is Jasmine. Jas-Min... Minnie. #$b# Plus with matching bows, it's like she's a little mini me!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R1.10": "Hmm...$3 #$b# I like it!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R2.1": "I'm sorry, Jas and I were talking and I offered to walk her home. #$b# Though I won't lie, I was curious how different the house looks now.$7",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R2.2": "Well, not much has changed. #$b# I waited for the day I'd see you back here at the ranch.$1 #$b# Now the only difference is the two of you have gotten older.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R2.3": "Aunt Marnie, you're gonna make me cry!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R2.4": "Don't cry, Miss Rosa! It's just a house!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.8": "Aunt Marnie, could Miss Rosa stay for dinner with us and @? #$b# Pretty please!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.9": "Of course! I'll set up another plate!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.10": "Oh, I don't want to impose.$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.11": "No, no. Stay... We can catch up.$6 #$b# @ can tell you all about how they saved my life.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.12": "Yawn! I wanna hear about how you met the Queen of Sauce!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.13": "That does sound more interesting.$1 #$b# But before you start, do you still hate cheese on everything except pizza, Rosa?$6",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.14": "Pretty much, but—$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.15": "*AH-CHOO!*",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.16": "Bless you.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.17": "Rosa, you okay?$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.18": "Yeah... just...a flare up...$6",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.19": "From a sneeze? Oh, Rosa, I didn't know your condition was that bad...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.20": "It can be... sometimes...$2 #$b# I'll be fine! The pain will go away... eventually... it just may take a few minutes...$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.21": "Rosa!$10",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.22": "Ow...$6 #$b# Sorry... that was embarrassing...$1 #$b#...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.23": "Are you okay, Miss Rosa?$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.24": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1}}#Of course, Minnie! I'm fi--$1|Of course, Jas! I'm fi--$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.25": "Rosa. Don't say you're fine. You're not fine.$5",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.Q2": "Rosalie looks like she's on the verge of tears. From embarassment, or pain, or both.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A3": "Suggest Rosalie lays down.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A4": "Urge Rosalie to go home.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A5": "Ask Rosalie how the pain feels on a scale from 1-20.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.1": "@ is right. You should lay down.$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.2": "You can lay down in Shane's room. I'll bring both of your dinners to you.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.3": "What do you mean my room?",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.4": "Huh? What?",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.5": "It's more comfortable than the couch, and I'm not allowing our guest to be left alone while she's in pain.$3 #$b# Besides, this way, you two can still catch up.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.6": "But I--$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.7": "No, Marnie's right... It's the same room as when we were kids...$2#$b# Do you need me to carry you or...?$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.8": "I'd like to see you try, but I can walk... I think...$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.9": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1})#There we go...$1 #$b# Sorry about dinner Minnie. I may not be fine now,$3 #$b# But I will be, okay? I promise.$1|There we go...$1 #$b# Sorry about dinner Jas. I may not be fine now,$3 #$b# But I will be, okay? I promise.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R3.10": "Okay. Get well soon, Miss Rosa!",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.1": "@ is right. You guys go ahead and eat dinner, I'll catch up.$3 #$b# I'm walking you home, Rosa.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.2": "But I--$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.3": "Rosa, please... #$b# I'm not gonna risk my goddaughter's new friend collapsing again.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.4": "I wanna come too!$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.5": "But then, who's gonna make sure that @ doesn't eat all the mash potatoes on me? Someone needs to keep watch!$1 #$b# Save me some, okay?$6",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.6": "Aw man, I'm missing out on Aunt Marnie's mash potatoes?! I've had dreams about those for twenty years!$8",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.7": "I'll bring some with me next time I'm in the saloon.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.8": "And you gotta get better real soon so we can watch the next Mortimer Rat Show together!$4",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R4.9": "I wouldn't miss it for the world!",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEVent.R4.10": "Take your time. I got you.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.1": "Um... an eleven...$2 #$b# No, maybe thirteen...$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.2": "Geez, Rosa, that doesn't sound good...$10",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.3": "1-20? Why not 1-10?$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.4": "Rosa's in pain all the time, so her pain tolerance is different than a regular person's. Her ten is different from ours.$3",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.5": "Farm Boy, how did you know that?$8",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.6": "You explained it in our first week of group therapy.$6 #$b# See? I pay attention sometimes.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.7": "Colour me impressed haha--$7 #$b# ow...$6",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.8": "Oh dear...why don't you lay down in Shane's room for a little bit?$ #$b# It's right there, same as the summers he stayed here.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.9": "Oh, I couldn't--$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.10": "Rosa, don't make me carry you.$11",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.11": "I'd like to see you try, but I can walk...",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.12": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1})#There we go...$1 #$b# Sorry about dinner Minnie. I may not be fine now,$3 #$b# But I will be, okay? I promise.$1|There we go...$1 #$b# Sorry about dinner Jas. I may not be fine now,$3 #$b# But I will be, okay? I promise.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.R5.13": "Get well soon, Miss Rosa!",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.26": "Oh dear... I hope the poor thing will be alright...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.27": "Well, no sense in us letting dinner go to waste. We should get eating before it gets cold.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.RosalieBed":"$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A4}}#Despite the earlier events, you, Jas, and Marnie ate a delicious dinner together. Rosalie wasn't well enough to get out of bed before you left, and Shane didn't join, but you could hear laughter from Shane's room. The kind of laughter you could only make with a close friend.",
"ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.28": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A4}}#Despite the earlier events, you, Jas, and Marnie ate a delicious dinner together. Shane came by shortly before you left, and let you know that Rosalie was recovering. His cheeks were pink from laughing with his old friend.|Despite the earlier events, you, Jas, and Marnie ate a delicious dinner together. Rosalie wasn't well enough to get out of bed before you left, and Shane didn't join, but you could hear laughter from Shane's room. The kind of laughter you could only make with a close friend.|Despite the earlier events, you, Jas, and Marnie ate a delicious dinner together. Shane came by shortly before you left, and let you know that Rosalie was recovering. His cheeks were pink from laughing with his old friend.",

//Shane x Rosalie -  Childhood Talk with Jas//

"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.1": "I'm glad Rosa was able to pay you a visit while I was at work.$6",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.2": "Yeah! She was feeling better so we had a tea party! #$b# Miss Rosa did all the voices for my dolls! Just like she does on the radio! She's really good at it!$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.3": "Wow, really? Well, she was always good at that.$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.4": "She's so funny, Uncle Shane... #$b# ...and really pretty!$4",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.5": "Well, um... I'm glad you like her.$3 #$b# What else did you guys talk about?$6",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.6": "I dunno...$3 #$b# Oh! Did you know she's a godmother, too? And she used to live in Vincent's house before the war!$4 #$b# So, she and Marnie were neighbours!$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.7": "Yeah, that tracks.$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.8": "I forgot to ask how you guys knew each other though...$3 #$b# Didn't you used to live in the city, Uncle Shane?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.9": "Yeah, I did, but I think I was around your age when I used to come here to help Marnie in the summers.$3 #$b# I did that for a few years since my parents... um...$2 #$b# couldn't watch me while they worked...$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.10": "Oh. Why didn't you guys talk until now?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.11": "Making friends as an adult is... complicated.$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.12": "But she's already your friend.$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.13": "Yes, well, Rosa was gone for a long time.$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.14": "Were you sad?$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.15": "Of course. She was my best friend for four years before she moved.$2 #$b# But I wasn't sad for long, cause that summer she left, I met your parents at Gridball camp.$6",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.16": "So, if my parents were alive, you'd talk to them?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.17": "Of course I would. I miss them every day, kid.$6 #$b# But, with Rosa, it was different.$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.18": "Different because she's a girl?$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.19": "$query PLAYER_GENDER Current Female#No no, Emily and @ are girls and I'm friends with them!$1|No, no, Emily is a girl, and I'm friend swith her!$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.20": "Is it because of her wheelchair she has sometimes?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.21": "Definitely not. I mean, it was a surprise since she didn't have it when we were kids.$1 #$b# But it's just a part of who she is now.$6",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.22": "I got it! #$b# It's cause she's the prettiest girl in Pelican Town! In the whole wide world!$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.23": "What? No!$10 #$b# I mean—-not that she's not pretty! She's very um...$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.24": "Uncle Shane your face is all red!$4 #$b# I knew it! You must have been in love with her! That's why--$1",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.25": "Jas.$11 #$b# ...*sigh*$2 #$b# Look, if Vincent told you he was going away for a long time, and you didn't know when you'd see him again, how would you feel?$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.26": "I'd be sad. But if he came back I'd talk to him.$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.27": "Well... What if you... got mad at each other before he left?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.28": "I'd be sadder...$2",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.29": "Exactly. Last time we saw each other, Rosa and I had... a fight.$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.30": "What about?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.31": "I... don't remember.$3 #$b# Probably something dumb, knowing me...$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.32": "But now she's back!$1 #$b# And you said you're sorry, right, Uncle Shane?$4",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.33": "Not yet...$2 #$b# ...But I will.$6",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.34": "Good.",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.35": "Uncle Shane?$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.36": "Yeah?",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.37": "... I'm happy you're feeling better...$3",
"ShaneRosalieChildhoodTalkJas.38": "Me too, kid.$6",

    //Shane's Low Day//

"ShaneRosalieLowDay.1": "Marnie, I told you, I'm just feeling low.$5",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.2": "Shane, you haven't eaten or drank anything all day.$2 #$b# #$b# At least, you haven't drank anything, as far as I know.$3 #$b# Can you blame me for worrying that you're not taking care of yourself?$3",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.3": "Oh, hi, @. Did you need something for the farm?",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.4": "He still gets this way sometimes...$2 #$b# I was hoping that with his sobriety and therapy, plus with Rosa moving back that he'd feel better, but today he hasn't left his room.$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.5": "Oh! Rosa! Are you looking for Shane?$1",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.6": "Yeah, he wasn't on the bus for therapy this morning. Is everything okay?$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.7": "It's just one of those days...$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.8": "Rosa? Urg, what do you want?$11",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.9": "I'm here to check on you. Are you okay, Farm Boy?$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.10": "Oh. How kind of you!$5 #$b# Let me guess, you want to know if I have any alcohol in here?$11",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.11": "No, actually. That's your choice if you want to break your sobriety...$3 #$b# Look you don't have to let me in, but you do need to take care of yourself.$3 #$b# I think you'd feel better if you at least ate something...$2",    
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.12": "I'd feel better if you actually liked me.$5",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.13": "What are you talking about?$8 #$b# Of course I like you! You're my best friend!$1",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.Q1": "Sorry, but it's true!",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A1": "None taken",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A2": "Um what?",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A3": "I saved Shane's life! I think I'M his best friend!",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.14": "Oh! Sure I am, Rosa!$11 #$b# What about what you said last night? How you couldn't stand the fact your ex was depressed and anxious all the time.$5 #$b# How his emotions burdened you? How his addiction was terrible, and when he quit, it was such an inconvenience to you!$5 #$b# How do you think I feel hearing the person I'm closest to say that about the man she loved, when I'm going through the same thing?$11 #$b# You might as well have said, 'It's too difficult to love someone so messed up'.$5",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.15": "Oh... Farm boy, no. No no no, that's not what I was saying.$8 #$b# I'm sorry. I didn't think about you and what you're going through. I should have been more sensitive talking about it.$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.16": "It's a little late for that.$11",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.17": "Well, let me make it right… $2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.18": "Yes, his pain, his anxieties, his low days were impositions. Especially on days when I needed him most.$2 #$b# But here's the difference between you two: He never wanted help. #$b# He chose to be defined by his shortcomings. That was his MO, Shane.$3 #$b# When things got too hard, he'd give up, or he'd magically want help so he could justify quitting, then refuse it when he had it...$2 #$b#...and he didn't see how much it was hurting me.$6 #$b# And I tried… I did everything to make him happy… nothing worked.$6 #$b# Shane, you're different.$3",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.19": "How?$3",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.20": "I'm sure taking in Jas terrified you, but you stepped up. #$b# When I became disabled, my ex wouldn't even get over his fear of driving and still made me drive myself to the hospital.$3 #$b# You're getting help. You see how your actions affect those you love, and you do what you think is best, even if you're not right all the time, but then you apologize and mean it. #$b# You're better at asking for help than even me.$1 #$b# It is hard to love somebody who doesn't want to change.$2 #$b# But you do. Being with you is the easiest thing in the world, Shane. It always has been, ever since we were kids. #$b# We were messed up kids… we're messed up adults, and yet, we're still here.$1 #$b# ... I'm still here...$2 #$b# And if you fall back into drinking, I'll still be here, Farm boy... I promise...$6",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.21": "Okay, I'm going to do what you ask and leave you alone.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.22": "Rosa!",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.23": "I know sometimes we just... need to be alone. #$b# I'm a bit much sometimes.$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.Q2": "It can be hard to be friends with someone like me.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A4": "That's not true!",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A5": "What are you talking about?",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.A6": "You're not too much.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.24": "You're surrounded by people all day—at work, at the saloon, and then you pretend everything's okay for Jas.$2 #$b# And you're exhausting yourself just trying to act normal for my benefit.$2 #$b# I'm sorry I've been selfish, I'm not the only one who needs days off...$2 #$b# Just know that I'm so grateful for you, Farm Boy... you make me feel... safe... you always have.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.25": "...$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.26": "Look, when you're ready, I'm here.$2 #$b# You can stay in your PJs if you want... #$b# Unless you're naked or in your underwear, then maybe put on a robe or something.$1",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.27": "*chuckle*",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.28": "Good, I can still make you laugh!$1 #$b# I'm gonna take care of the chickens and help your aunt with some chores. Just call out when you're ready, okay? #$b# And if you need anything at all let me know... #$b# Even if it's to leave you alone forever. I'll do it if that's what you want.$2",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.29": "Oh, and one more thing.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.30": "They had pizza at group therapy from that place you were talking about in Zuzu City. #$b# I saved you some. It's by the door.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.31": "I don't think Charlie is used to you yet. She'll probably kill you if I'm not there.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.32": "Bold of you to assume I'd lose in a chicken fight.",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.33": "Bold of you to assume I'd let you win against Charlie.$6",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.34": "You brought me four slices?!$10",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.35": "Honestly, two are mine. I skipped lunch so you could see my reaction.$1 #$b# But if you were sick, I was gonna eat them in front of you.$9",
"ShaneRosalieLowDay.36": "What was that you said about giving me space? Is it too late for that?$3",


//Dreams And Disasters//

"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.1": "$query PLAYER_HAS_MAIL Current {{ModId}}_ShaneBeforeRosalieFlag Received#I'm so sorry you were going through that, Shane. I'm glad @ was there to help you.$2|I'm so sorry you were going through that, Shane. I'm glad @ was there to help you.$2 #$b# If I'd know how bad it was, I would have reached out sooner.$6",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.2": "$query PLAYER_HAS_MAIL Current {{ModId}}_ShaneBeforeRosalieFlag Received#No, I'm glad you never saw me like that.$2#$b# I'll take you seeing me go through temper tantrums as a kid over you seeing me in such a dark place now.$3 #$b# Maybe it wouldn't have been so dark if you stayed when that was all happening,$2 #$b# But you're here now. Even when I slip up... You always were when we were kids.$6|No, don't feel bad... We were both shy kids growing up.$6 #$b# Figures as adults, we'd be too awkward to talk.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.3": "We didn't have friends as kids... but we had each other... #$b# Maybe we have other friends now, but honestly, I think I missed you more than anyone else I've lost along the way...$2 #$b# I don't' expect you to say it back. But it's true for me.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.4": "Rosa...$2#$b# I've been meaning to ask you, and you don't need to tell me but...$3 #$b# ...$2#$b# ...$2#$b# Did he ever...$2#$b# ...$2 #$b#... Did he ever... hurt you?$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.5": "He did. Didn't he.$3",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.6": "Once...",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.7": "That's why you left, right?$3",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.8": "Rosa! Why didn't you—$10",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.9": "Does Gus know? Will the guy try and come after you?$3",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.10": "No... and no, he's not dangerous...$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.11": "So, who does know?$3",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.12": "Just my sister. And Harvey... And now you.$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.13": "Rosa, I wish I was...$2 #$b# ...$2 #$b#I can't...$11 #$b# ... I don't...$5",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.14": "I'm sorry. I'm not mad at you... I promise. #$b# The important thing is you're out of there.$2 #$b# And you're not going back to him, right?$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.15": "No. It's over. It should have been over years ago...$3 #$b# Love makes you do crazy things... including staying when logic says you shouldn't...$2 #$b# I defended him for so long that... I guess I didn't want to believe what everyone was saying...$2 #$b# Because, if they're right, that means you were dumb enough to fall for it...$3 #$b# I know, it's a tale as old as time. But it's true.$3",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.16": "Shane gently takes Rosalie's hand.",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.17": "I know...$2 #$b# You don't need to explain, Rosa. He's gone. You suffered enough. You don't need I told you sos. #$b# I know you hear that voice inside you telling you the same thing.$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.18": "I'm here for you, Rosa. I'm here in Stardew Valley to stay.$6 #$b# Not just for the summers anymore, I'm not going anywhere...$6 #$b# And Marnie is here for you too, as always.$6 #$b# You also have Jas as a new best friend, so you're stuck with her as long as you're living here.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.19": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1}}#That's not a bad thing, I love Minnie!$1|That's not a bad thing, I love Jas!$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.20": "I missed this... Sitting in silence and it not feeling awkward...$6 #$b# I'm glad that hasn't changed.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.21": "Me too, Farm Boy...#$b# ...and thanks for taking me outside. Having a wheelchair sucks a little less with you being understanding.$7 #$b# And not feeling like a burden...$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.22": "I'm glad I could help, Rosa.$6 #$b# We said we'd always be there for each other. We just had a bit of a break.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.23": "Exactly! #$b# ... But if I ever become too much—$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.24": "I know. But honestly, Rosa... I doubt you ever will be.$6",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.25": "Same here.",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.26": "Hey, Farm Boy?",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.27": "Yeah?",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.28": "...$4 #$b# ...$2 #$b# ...You're still my best friend.$1",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.29": "$query !PLAYER_NPC_RELATIONSHIP Any Shane Married Engaged#... Rosa...$2 #$b#...I...$6 #$b#...I want...$4 #$b# umm...$2|Rosa... can we um...$2",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.30": "$query !PLAYER_NPC_RELATIONSHIP Any Shane Married Engaged#*sigh*... you too.$2|Never mind... I just wanted to say that I'm glad you and @ get along so well.$3 #$b# You both mean a lot to me.$6",
"ShaneRosalieDreamsAndDisasters.31": "How are you, on a scale from 1-20? Your arm is looking better.$6",





//Sleep Over//

"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.1": "Go back to sleep. I'll see you later okay? Rest up. I mean it.",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.2": "@! What are you—$10 #$b# Don't sneak up on a guy like that!$5",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.Q1": "What? Why are you looking at me like that?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A1": "What are you doing at the saloon this early?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A2": "Do I want to know?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A3": "What are you hiding?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A4": "I thought you were sober!",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.3": "It's not what you think!$10 #$b# I just...$3",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.4": "I had... the urge last night... and I came here wanting a drink.$11",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.5": "I know, I know, but...$11 #$b# Rosa was working and...$3 #$b# ...she was pushing herself too hard...$3 #$b# She was smiling, cracking jokes, but I could tell she was struggling...$2 #$b# It wasn't busy so I hung out with her, made sure she rested, and she made sure I didn't drink and...$2 #$b# Well, I stayed the night. We were both... tired, I guess.$3",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.Q2": "*Shane isn't looking at your face*",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A5": "You know she's married right?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A6": "I'm glad you two are supporting each other.",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A7": "How is she now?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.A8": "How are you now?",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.R5": "Yeah, I know. But it's over. She has a lawyer and everything. #$b# The guy even has a girlfriend now, if you can believe it!$3 #$b# You know, I thought I was pathetic, but this guy was something else...$11 #$b# Wait, what does her being married have to do with—-$5",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.R6": "Yeah. It's crazy that we still... get each other.$1 #$b# I was scared that with how messed up our lives turned out that we wouldn't fall into the same rhythm.$2 #$b# But somehow, it feels like no time has passed.$6 #$b# Things are just... lighter, I guess... Even when we talk about the heavy stuff.$4 #$b# I'm happy she's in my life... and Jas is too... #$b# *ahem* We're... good for each other I guess...$3",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.R7": "Good, I think.$6 #$b# I mean, she could wake up feeling awful but, last night, we kinda just... hung out.$2 #$b# I know she's good at hiding her pain and when something bothers her, but honestly, I see it clearly.$2 #$b# Its like looking in a... weird mirror, I don't know.$3 #$b# She can somehow read me too. Ever since we were kids...$6 #$b# We've always been good at that...$4",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.R8": "Tired. Better. Glad I didn't do it.$2 #$b# We just watched TV all night. Played some video games that weren't so hard on her hands. #$b# Then we just... talked.$3 #$b# I don't even remember falling asleep. We used to do that all the time as kids. It just happened.$6 #$b# It sucks that our lives went sideways but,$2 #$b# I feel like Rosa... I don't know... doesn't see me as broken or something to fix.$6 #$b# I don't see her like that either.$6",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.6": "Hold on! You don't think—$10 #$b# @, It's not like that!$5 #$b# I don't—-$5 #$b# I can't—-$11 #$b# She—-$2",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.7": "Buh…$2 #$b# @, you're the closest friend I've got besides Rosa.$3 #$b# So, be honest with me... #$b# Do you think that...$2 #$b# I mean, I don't... want to ruin anything between me and Rosa after we finally got close again.$3 #$b# But… do you think that she could...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSleepOver.8": "Never mind. Forget I said anything… $3 #$b# I need to go sleep... in my own bed.... before I say something stupid. Before Marnie and Jas notice...$3",
"ShaneRosaliesSleepover.9": "Don't say anything to Rosa. Okay? I don't want her getting more anxious...",



//Sandcastles With Jas//

"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.1": "You know, I used to make sandcastles all the time with your Uncle Shane when I was your age.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.2": "Do you come here often, Miss Rosa?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.3": "Whenever I can, it's harder some days than others.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.4": "Why? Doesn't the water help you?$3 #$b# You know, with the pain of walking on land?$3",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.5": "Hey, @! Good to see you!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.Q1": "Can you help me with something?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.A1": "What is it?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.A2": "I'm kinda busy.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.A3": "You mean commit robbery? You only need one ribbon, Jas.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.6": "I'm trying to get Miss Rosa to confess!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.7": "Confess what?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.8": "You know, Miss Rosa... I can keep a secret.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.9": "Is that so?$9",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.10": "Like that Uncle Shane listens to your show every morning before work! #$b# And Vincent's brother, Sam, his name is Samson!$4",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.11": "Oops!...$3 #$b# Well, I won't tell anyone your secrets!$1 #$b# Besides, no one would believe me 'cause I'm a kid!$4",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.12": "Believe you about what?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.13": "Come on!I Miss Rosa, I think it's pretty obvious.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.14": "Oh...?$8 #$b# ...Have you told your Uncle Shane?$2",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.15": "Yeah... But he doesn't believe me...$2",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.Q2": "You believe me, right?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.A4": "Of course!",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.A5": "I prefer cold hard facts.",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.16": "Wow... maybe I am easy to read...$2 #$b# But you got me!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.17": "So you admit it! It's true!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.18": "Yeah... just don't tell your uncle, okay?$1 #$b# You too, @!$3",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.19": "AHHH!!",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.20": "I knew it I knew it I knew it!!!$1 #$b# Don't worry Miss Rosa, your secret is safe with me!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.21": "Hey Jas! Hey @!$6 #$b# Rosa, I thought I said no sugar after six!$3",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.22": "Uncle Shane! Miss Rosa—-",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.23": "Yeah?$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.24": "... I can't tell you. I promised I wouldn't.$4",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.25": "*sigh* Rosa, did you tell Jas you're a mermaid?",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.26": "What? No!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.27": "Yes you did! Right @?$1 #$b# @ was here when she confessed! You didn't believe me, but I told you!$4",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.28": "I uh... gotta go... Uncle Gus is expecting me for dinner.$2",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.29": "You want me to walk you home?$6",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.30": "No no, I'm okay. You guys finish up the sand castle. I think it needs a moat. #$b# See you guys around!$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.31": "Am I gonna have a mermaid as my new aunt?$3",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.32": "Not unless you know any.$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.33": "So, if Miss Rosa was a mermaid, you'd marry her?$4",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.34": "I think if she was a mermaid she'd tell me.$1 #$b# And even if she was, we're just friends.$6",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.35": "Then why do you have that stupid grin on your face?$1",
"ShaneRosalieSandcastles.36": "Enough with the questions, kid.$11",








//Kitchen Love//
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.1": "I don't know why Jas likes you so much.",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.2": "What's not to like? I'm adorable.$9",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.3": "You know you say you've changed but honestly, you haven't. Not really.$6",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.4": "You too. You're the same, but different.",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.5": "You mean, the bags under my eyes and my beer gut.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.6": "I mean, you're still a grump, but I can still manage to make you smile. #$b# Your sense of humour hasn't changed. #$b# And yeah, you're older, been through the ringer, but that's just what twenty years does to you.$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.7": "And you're still shy yet can't shut up with me around.$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.8": " You're still listening, aren't you?$1 #$b# You're... probably the only person I've met who does.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.9": "What are you doing?",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.10": "The dishes?$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.11": "Don't worry about that. I'll take care of it after you leave.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.12": "Rosa? What's wrong?$10",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.13": "I'm fine, I'm just... thinking about things.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.14": "I hope it's not my lack of cooking skills. Sorry, I made just a frozen pizza.$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.15": "Hey now, it was frozen pizza and you *added* things to it!$1 #$b# That's a drastic improvement to the frozen box foods my ex used to cook for me every night. And he was a cook!$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.16": "Ouch. That on top of everything else...$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.17": "I know, I know. I married a loser. Shouldn't have stayed. I deserve so much better and all that.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.18": "You've been talking to your mom again, haven't you?$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.19": "Robin, actually. As you can tell, she's very supportive. I know she means well... #$b# You know, I just haven't spoken to him since that day... and it's becoming more real.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.20": "You know, I noticed that we talk a lot about me and my depression and anxiety...$2 #$b# But you kind of... avoid talking about him in the end. I mean, you do in therapy, kind of. But I try not to...",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.21": "I appreciate that more than you know, Farm Boy. #$b# What do you want to know? I can handle it.$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.22": "I don't know... What did you see in him? #$b# I mean, you clearly loved the guy to put up with what you did. I just want to know.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.23": "You know, when I was a teenager I read somewhere that the reason you fall in love with someone sometimes becomes the reason you fall out of love with them.#$b# Like, they're spontaneous and then you realize how reckless they are, and you can't make plans.$2 #$b# Or, you love how much they love their family, then they prioritize them over you, even if you're in the middle of a crisis and need support, that kind of thing...$2 #$b# In my case, he was an emotional and sensitive person.$3 #$b# You know, he wasn't afraid to cry or tell me how he felt. He loved openly and freely...$1 #$b#... and after a while, it became crippling to him. I was his entire world...$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.24": "Oh... I see. He couldn't let you go.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.25": "Wouldn't.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.26": "Wouldn't, sorry... #$b# Well, I'm glad you're not with him anymore, with that and everything else...$2 #$b# I learned a long time ago that real love is putting someone else's needs before yours.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.27": "No I don't believe that.$3 #$b# He did that, or he thought he did, and it destroyed us both.$3 #$b# You need to take care of yourself too...$2 #$b# Not that he believed me, even when I told him what it was doing to me, to us... He wouldn't.$3 #$b# He would resent me for all the things he did to help me. That he said he did 'for' me.$3 #$b# And it just poisoned us...$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.28": "It's okay not to be okay... #$b# But if you're not helping yourself, not trying to be the best person you can be for that person, especially when it matters,$2 #$b# Then you not being okay is at the expense of someone else. And that's not love to me, because, why would you do that to the person you love?$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.29": "I don't want to burden anyone. #$b# But if you burden yourself then... I guess it spills out anyway...$2 #$b# It took me a long time to realize that... too long.$2#$b# I'm glad that you weren't there to see me like that.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.30": "And I'm sure Jas and Marnie are happier, right? Now that you're happy?",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.31": "Yeah. I guess so.$6",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.32": "$query !PLAYER_NPC_RELATIONSHIP Any Shane Divorced#Enough about me though. I can't believe I never asked, but have you ever gotten married?$1|Enough about me though...$1 #$b# Speaking of exes... You don't mind me and and your ex being friends, right?$1 #$b# I can't imagine seeing your ex every day... Do you think you'll get married again?",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.33": "$query !PLAYER_NPC_RELATIONSHIP Any Shane Divorced#Not even close. I haven't dated anyone since... #$b# I think since around the time I took in Jas. After her parents passed...$3 #$b# Marnie's been on me about that, but between work, and Jas, the chickens, I don't have time.|I don't mind, I mean, we wouldn't be talking if it weren't for them...#$b# But before them, I hadn't dated anyone since... I think since around the time I took in Jas. #$b# Marnie's been on me about that, but between work, and Jas, the chickens, I don't have time.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.34": "You make time for me.$7",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.35": "Yeah, but you're different. I don't need to spend as much mental or physical energy with you.$1 #$b# We just, kinda, hang out. I like being around you.$6 #$b# You don't mind that I'm damaged...$6 #$b# It wouldn't be fair to put my baggage on some poor person who isn't my therapist.$3 #$b# Besides I'm not exactly a catch.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.36": "Hey, you're not allowed to speak for us women... Or men if you're into them.$1 #$b# Maybe I can't speak for them either as I'm getting a divorce with my high school sweetheart.$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.37": "$p {{i18n:ShaneRosalieSneezeEvent.A1}}#But honestly, Farm Boy, the fact that you're working on yourself, and you took in Minnie and basically fathering her, #$b# Plus, not only you see the flaws within yourself but you're working to fix them... #$b# You have one of the biggest hearts I've ever known. And you're going to make someone very happy one day. I know it.$4|But honestly, Farm Boy, the fact that you're working on yourself, and you took in Jas and basically fathering her, #$b# Plus, not only you see the flaws within yourself but you're working to fix them... #$b# You have one of the biggest hearts I've ever known. And you're going to make someone very happy one day. I know it.$4", 
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.38": "Thanks, Rosa... I think you would too.$4",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.39": "I don't think so...$2 #$b# The idea of dating and falling in love again...$2 #$b# Being vulnerable and open, just to get manipulated and gas lit and forced to think of every moment and decision of my life to include someone else...$3 #$b# I get anxious thinking about it..." ,
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.40": "You're never going to date again?$3 #$b# Rosa, I know you. You were planning your wedding when we were ten!$1",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.41": "I wasn't disabled or fat when I was ten, or when I met my ex.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.42": "Rosa, can you just listen for a minute without putting yourself down?$11 #$b# Yes, you're disabled, and you're not... whatever the average weight is for a woman our age.$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.43": "Thanks, but listen.$3 #$b# You're also kind. You're one of the smartest people I know.$6 #$b# You're talented in... so many things, I can't keep track but I'm trying... $1 #$b# You're funny, and sweet... #$b# And... I think Jas mentioned something about you being ‘really pretty'$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.44": "Is that so?$9",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.45": "Well, Jas is a terrible liar. So, it must be the truth...$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.46": "Well, tell her I said thanks.$4",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.47": "I will...$4",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.48": "Shane puts his hand to Rosalie's face and moves slightly closer.",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.49": "...$2 #$b# Farm Boy?$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.50": "Yeah?$4",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.51": "You're... a little close...$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.52": "Sorry... I know you just said...$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.53": "No! It's fine!... We've um...$1 #$b# ...$2", 
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.54": "You know, I've been meaning to apologize for the last day we saw each other as kids.$2 #$b# I shouldn't have done that... I know we were young but, it doesn't excuse it, and I'm sorry.$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.55": "Oh um...$3 #$b# I don't even remember what happened...$3",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.56": "You don't?$8",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.57": "Yeah, not everyone has a perfect memory like you, Rosa.$11 #$b# It was twenty years ago. I had other things on my mind besides you.$5",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.58": "Right... Well, I'm sorry, all the same...$2",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.59": "I'm gonna go... I'm really tired...$2 #$b# Goodnight, Shane...$11",
"ShaneRosalieKitchen.60": "Buh..."

